text:
DANTE FIGHT TIPS

I know I'm 4 days late but I might as well do it if there's a chance gura sees this:

Defensive
- When Dante fires his guns from one side of the screen to another, you can jump over it
- When Dante spins his guns and fires from down to up, you can dodge roll
- side note for the 2 tips above, him shooting his guns are the same from the tutorial from mission 1. If you dodge them successfully by either jumping or rolling, he won't lock on and put holes into you.
- It's best to not shoot Dante with Nero's regular shots, he'll deflect them with his own bullets and eventually stinger when he gets close enough to you
- Don't shoot him when he's in royal guard either, he'll use ur bullets to build his royal guard meter and release the damage back towards you when you attack him with your sword. In case you do accidentally shoot him, wait until he changes to another style before attacking

Offensive
- while Dante can change styles in this fight, when he is in trickster or royal guard, 
It is very easy to use snatch (lock on + buster) and pull him in, and you can quickly follow up with a buster (no lock on)
- Dante's stinger can actually be countered with buster (no lock on) if you time it correctly, though it isn't recommended to do so since it's a little tricky
- Buster while in devil trigger will immediately slam him into the ground 3 times and deal a lot of damage. And regular buster puts you into the clash animation, if you don't spam buster while in this animation, you won't do damage and Dante will counter you instead.
- Nero does a 4 hit combo with a knock back move for the 4th hit, so it'll be better to maximize the damage you do by bustering him after 3 hits instead of trying to do it after knocking him back.

Others
- ALWAYS REMEMBER DEVIL TRIGGER, Nero's devil trigger can help you escape Dante's combos and deal some damage to him with the explosion from activating devil trigger
- GOOD LUCK AND HAVE FUN (seriously, you're gonna need the luck part)

Gura the number one rule to fight M10 Dante is that he can only be hit when he is attacking. If you want to hit him you have to lure his attack, dodge and hit him immediately after.

Or there's a cheesy tactics that you can grap him when he jumps, and he must jump if you stay on the roof.

If you go see videos on YouTube most of them does it for show, doing flashy moves and dangerous parties. You will probably get confused, so just remember this rule when you try.

text:
Excellent work against Agnus, that was exactly the grade of aggression you needed. :_gurapat: The only difference between your performance in that fight and a high tier players' is that they memorized all the tells and attack patterns. They're dodging between every attack because they've played the fight dozens of times. As long as you're peeling the enemy's health faster than they're taking yours you're still doing great!

That Dante fight is made to punish players who overuse jump invulnerability frames and turn a forward-moving fighting style against the player. Most of his attacks have a shallow arc with a long range while Nero's attacks tend to have a wide arc with a shorter range. Lateral dodges will put you behind him while he's attacking and give you a window of opportunity to hit him. Careful though, he adapts using his styles.

author: @thebubs5579

text:
Notes about Dante 2: (edited: additional notes)

- Spamming moves is actively discouraged, since Dante has a response to most of Nero's moves/abilities that are tricky to avoid. Streak has no practical against Dante use since it will almost certainly end in a whiff, but you can dodge out of the situation if you're feeling lucky.

- Side Rolls are extremely helpful if timed correctly, since they position Nero for sword combos or snatch into buster

- Yes, Nero's gun will counter Dante's guns, but ONLY if Dante's directly aiming at Nero from the get-go. If he's doing a fanning sweep with Ebony and Ivory, it's better to jump over the fire and attempt an air-snatch into buster. That said: avoid being the one to initiate any gunfights to be safe.

- Buster can counter Stinger if timed correctly. Alternatively, jump out of the way and air-snatch into buster.

- Exceed's quirk of slightly faster attack animations can catch Dante off guard, provided that Nero closes the distance first without Dante doing anything odd (especially if he's in Trickster).

- Royalguard is surprisingly easy to handle since Dante doesn't really attack all that much in RG. Walk up to Dante and pull an air-snatch before breaking out the Buster (Dante can still shoot Nero out of the air in RG tho). 

- Devil Trigger will break Nero out of Rebellion combos in a pinch.
